":{"pid":"e4ab43c0766d848847829404c6fd20622aa2313e","tid":2358791,"uid":191926,"like":15,"dislike":0,"score":15,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2021-01-08T13:12:18.000Z","msg":"韓日兩國2015年底曾針對慰安婦問題達成協議，日方針對涉及慰安婦的罪行公開致歉，並撥款10億日圓協助南韓政府成立支援慰安婦的基金會，時任日本首相安倍晉三也以首相身分公開謝罪並表示反省，當時安倍與時任南韓總統朴槿惠均對協議給予正面評價。<br />\n<br />\n其實日本係應該道歉+賠款<br />\n問題係人地已經道左歉+賠左錢<br />\n<br />\n仲要你地個政府都同意左<br />\n<br />\n無理由換左人就又要你道歉同賠錢<br />\n<br />\n利申 對南韓人，日本人兩者係比較中性"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-01-09T06:50:16.000Z","msg":"同支那一撚樣 明明簽撚左中日友好條約 日本又係支那投資代替賠償 點知之後反面 小日本小日本咁叫<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"d611604a65fa21a829a08737f1de95c90a7f7961","tid":2358791,"uid":119393,"like":10,"dislike":0,"score":10,"quote":{"pid":"1b4038eff3530de18b68309aa7cb9b7ea002c432","tid":2358791,"uid":81575,"like":1,"dislike":7,"score":-6,"quote":{"pid":"40eb969b5aab68a0793f730cd437b902d5d5b473","tid":2358791,"uid":197393,"like":22,"dislike":11,"score":11,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2021-01-08T11:27:07.000Z","msg":"韓狗on99"},"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2021-01-08T13:42:25.000Z","msg":"on9個位係邊?"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-01-09T08:05:35.000Z","msg":"再post一次:<br />\n1965年傾日韓基本條約<br />\n日本要求對所有韓國人直接單對單賠償<br />\n南韓政府拒絕左, 要日本政府lump sum一次過交比南韓政府<br />\n南韓政府仲話朝鮮半島只有一個國家要拎埋北韓果份, 日本話ok<br />\n南韓政府再話呢D內容係機密, 你唔好公開, 日本都ok<br />\n最後日本政府就將現金加低息貸款加所有日本人在朝鮮半島資產交晒比南韓政府作為朝鮮半島所有受害者賠償<br />\n條約白紙黑字寫明最終且不可逆<br />\n點知轉頭南韓政府就使晒D錢搞基建搞國企, 一個仙都冇分比國民<br />\n仲隱瞞日本政府已經比左錢, 四十幾年來一直叫國民向日本追討<br />\n日本政府心地善良由南韓人屌足四十幾年都遵守承諾唔公開真相<br />\n直到2005年南韓政府外交文件夠期解密<br />\n南韓政府用盡手段阻止條約談判內容公開甚至連&quot;公開會對國家不利&quot;都講埋, 結果都要公開, 全世界呢刻先知日本原來真係比左錢<br />\n有南韓人根據公開內容告南韓政府, 南韓法院判過左時效<br />\n然後有南韓人告已經比左錢既日本政府, 南韓法院居然判要再比!<br />\n仲有<br />\n果D唔係強徵勞工<br />\n係當年朝鮮大學生示威抗議朝鮮族無得去兵工廠賺錢先開post<br />\n仲要幾十人搶一個位<br />\n<br />\n以上資料中英日維基都有<br />\n<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_on_Basic_Relations_between_Japan_and_the_Republic_of_Korea\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FTreaty_on_Basic_Relations_between_Japan_and_the_Republic_of_Korea&d=vGGWHGA7%2F8HunCPhnXLTIaix4Ji0%2BaXPUR6dcaOs6Zo%3D&h=af1334b2\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_on_Basic_Relations_between_Japan_and_the_Republic_of_Korea</a><br />\n<br />\nIn January 2005, the South Korean government disclosed 1,200 pages of diplomatic documents that recorded the proceeding of the treaty. The documents, kept secret for 40 years, recorded that the Japanese government actually proposed to the South Korean government to directly compensate individual victims but it was the South Korean government which insisted that it would handle individual compensation to its citizens and then received the whole amount of grants on behalf of the victims.[9][10][11]<br />\n<br />\nThe South Korean government demanded a total of 364 million dollars in compensation for the 1.03 million Koreans conscripted into the workforce and the military during the colonial period,[12] at a rate of 200 dollars per survivor, 1,650 dollars per death and 2,000 dollars per injured person.[13] South Korea agreed to demand no further compensation, either at the government or individual level, after receiving $800 million in grants and soft loans from Japan as compensation for its 1910&ndash;45 colonial rule in the treaty.[11]<br />\n<br />\nHowever, the South Korean government used most of the grants for economic development,[14] failing to provide adequate compensation to victims by paying only 300,000 won per death in compensating victims of forced labor between 1975 and 1977.[13] Instead, the government spent most of the money establishing social infrastructures, founding POSCO, building Gyeongbu Expressway and the Soyang Dam with the technology transfer from Japanese companies.[15] This investment was named Miracle on the Han River in South Korea.<br />\n<br />\nAs the result of this revelation[according to whom?], there have been growing calls for the South Korean government to compensate the victims. A survey conducted shortly after the disclosure showed that more than 70 percent of South Koreans believe the South Korean government should bear responsibility to pay for those victims. The South Korean government announced that it will establish a team to deal with the appeals for compensation, although &quot;It has been the government's position that compensation for losses during the Japanese occupation has already been settled&quot;.[12]"},{"pid":"b9aaad37e89c13f05415116e1dcd455cabb7028e","tid":2358791,"uid":217565,"like":0,"dislike":2,"score":-2,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-01-09T08:17:00.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/O9fOW1F.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FO9fOW1F.jpg&h=cdd0b613&s={SIZE}\" /> 其實係想佢地道歉<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"efa9c5ac63761b760fa31c8f7382cbab9b21727e","tid":2358791,"uid":180462,"like":0,"dislike":1,"score":-1,"quote":{"pid":"3e10cd2a49aab09b89d2756559c7c7f6eb49e87f","tid":2358791,"uid":262035,"like":28,"dislike":0,"score":28,"quote":{"pid":"2792d1b4b38b83d52bf43853feaa8a98fbc32c21","tid":2358791,"uid":351130,"like":13,"dislike":15,"score":-2,"quote":{"pid":"7cfe181ab2c379588957802229367f071836ead1","tid":2358791,"uid":331421,"like":0,"dislike":8,"score":-8,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-01-08T12:15:54.000Z","msg":"1億韓元真係好平，咪爽手畀左佢<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2021-01-08T12:23:33.000Z","msg":"唔係錢嘅問題 係日本角度 <br />\n賠錢即係承認有發生過捉韓國人做慰安婦 因為日本想篡改歴史"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-01-08T12:42:06.000Z","msg":"咪鳩up啦<br />\n日本承應咗同道咗歉<br />\n而且國家層面上面賠償咗<br />\n<br />\n而家民事追討日本政府根本無法理依據<br />\n情況好似你伯爺得罪人但好多年前settle咗<br />\n而家突然又走嚟問你追債咁<br />\n點睇都唔fair 啦<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-01-09T09:07:30